thread.title: Pokes stun Lions at home 21 - 7 remaining unbeaten

author: Mike Gaither
title: Pokes stun Lions at home 21 - 7 remaining unbeaten
text:
Pokes stun Lions at home 21 - 7 - KPLC 7 News, Lake Charles, Louisiana Member Center: Pokes stun Lions at home 21 - 7 remaining unbeaten Posted: mgaither@kplctv.com LAKE CHARLES, LA (KPLC) - 
The Pokes stun the Lions in Cowboy Stadium tonight defeating Southeastern 21 - 7 to improve to 5 - 0 on the season. 
Cowboys Ryan Ross lead the way on the ground for McNeese with 15 carries and 149 yards, including two touchdowns. 
QB Daniel Sams had 22 carries for 75 yards as the Pokes knock off SLU in a tight ball game. 
McNeese will hit the road next week to take on Central Arkansas at 6pm on Saturday. Can't Find Something?
